commit.message:
Handle disappearing interfaces

When an interface disappears handle the resulting POLLERR
result from polling. Ignoring this will cause ndppd to go into
a hot loop.

This is a very simple fix that will make the daemon terminate.

Added init script working on Debian Jessie, just copy the file to
/etc/init.d/ndppd. Probably works on current stable as well, but
I couldn't test this so far.

Fix issue #39, configure interfaces after daemonization, as otherwise we
loose the ALLMULTI flag on the listening interfaces during the whole process.
Probable cause is the parent restoring the original state of the interface
flags before exitting.

commit.message:
Merge pull request #30 from john-sharratt/master

Feature to automatically wire the routes for a gateway
Doing some debugging on an issue with the routes not working from gateway hosted IPs
Added a fix to stop nasty NDP loops when being proactive on the NDP adverts
Added session keepalive with retries that will ensure the routes are kept up during high traffic when no proactive NDP soliciations are sent by the sender
Added some documentation on why autowire does not work with static and auto rules defined in the configuration
NDP proxy will now respond to Solicitation requests to gateway addresses that it holds on secondary interfaces
Added a global list of all the IP addresses that the interfaces of the local machine which will be used to cover some missing solicitation requests
Now creating session on receiving NDP adverts even if no one has specifically asked for one yet thus ensuring the routes are created and that the latecy on proxy solicitation is kept much lower
Was touching all the sessions rather than the one that had an solicitation request causing none of the sessions to really expire
Added additional logging on system calls and ensured that an error message rather than an error code is returned for easier debugging
Added some additional debug information that help help track down what triggers a particular failure path
Now restoring the promiscuous state of the interface when the appliance terminates
Now restoring the promiscuous state of the interface when the appliance terminates
Added a promiscuous mode that allows the proxy interface to also respond to queries send from the gateway (for instance when it needs to route to a WAN address thats local)
The manual had the wrong setting name for autowire

Changelog updated

Updated the changelog so that it reflects the pull request and describes what has changed in much more detail
Now properly exiting if any of the interfaces are not opened rather than silently continuing
Now daemonizing after the configuration rather than before so that more errors are caught on the command line rather than via an ASYNC process
Now only unwiring if the NDP proxy did the wiring in the first place
